cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper focuses on distributed computing systems and proposes a method to combat computational heterogeneity in such systems. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the use of work exchange to optimize the task assignment in distributed computing systems, which involves the use of algorithms and data structures. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a method to improve the time efficiency of distributed computing systems, which can be seen as a control problem. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper involves the use of communication and coordination among distributed nodes, which is related to networking and internet architecture. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper presents a lower bound on the expected computation time based on the work-conservation principle, which is related to information theory.
